The course defines the concept of culture and intercultural communication. Methods and principles of cross-cultural learning are analyzed. A special attention will be given to the Estonian school situation where students with different language background are thought. Case studies are analyzed in order to find solutions applicable in school stages I and II.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To get a general overview about intercultural communication and development of ideas of multilingual education in Estonian and worldwide context. To support future teachers readiness to work in multicultural and -lingual classroom.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  To pass the course successfully the student: * knows basic theoretical principles of intercultural communication;  * is aware of good practices in supporting multilingual pupils in Estonian schools; * understands how multicultural background influences learning process;  * knows  principles and methods of cross-cultural studies;  * can use appropriate teaching strategies based on the needs of students with different language background.
